-- Chinese leader to visit U.S. in January
-- 
-- Thu Sep 23, 2010 3:05pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/09/23/us-usa-china-visit-idUSTRE68M4OB20100923

 

 UNITED NATIONS  (Reuters) - President Barack Obama has invited Chinese President Hu Jintao to the United States for a state visit in January, a U.S. official said on Thursday. 

 Jeffrey Bader, the senior National Security Council official for Asia, told reporters that the Chinese government had accepted the invitation. (Reporting by  Steve Holland , editing by Missy Ryan)